==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tupian
<hw>Tu"pi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Designating, or
pertaining to, a linguistic stock of South American Indians comprising
the most important Brazilian tribes. Agriculture, pottery, and stone
working were practiced by them at the time of the conquest. The Tupi and
the Guarani were originally the most powerful of the stock, which is
hence also called <altname>Tupi-Guaranian</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tupman</ent>⟦br⟧
